      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried putting these checks in, but none of the test images I have + none of the sksp images I had contained curves matching to these in lutntype profiles.\n\nI also tried putting more generalized linear checks here and not a single image with an AtoBType or XYZTRC seemed to specify linear gamma by a table (besides via count\u003d0), at least within the color_space_almost_equal error margin. This is probably due to the fact that in non-lutnType profiles you can simply avoid putting in a table in the first place (ie 0 offset), or you can encode linear by having a count of 0. This is not the case for lutntype, hence the incredible amount of linear tables.",
